# React (Web) to Expo React Native + GlueStack UI Conversion Guide

## Overview

This guide covers converting a React web application to a **React Native app using Expo + GlueStack UI v2**. GlueStack UI is a universal component library that works on both web and React Native — it provides styled, accessible components (Button, Input, Box, Text, Card, etc.) that replace both HTML elements and raw React Native primitives. This is the "component library" path rather than writing StyleSheets by hand.

Read `react-to-expo-react-native.mdc` first for the foundational React → React Native conversion rules. This guide focuses specifically on how GlueStack UI replaces manual StyleSheet work.

## Tech Stack

- **Expo**: SDK 55+
- **React Native**: 0.83+ (New Architecture required)
- **Expo Router**: v4.x
- **GlueStack UI**: v2.x (`@gluestack-ui/themed`)
- **NativeWind**: v4.x (GlueStack v2 uses NativeWind/Tailwind under the hood)
- **React**: 19.x
- **TypeScript**: 5.x

---

## Why GlueStack UI

| Raw React Native | GlueStack UI |
|-----------------|--------------|
| Write `StyleSheet.create()` for everything | Pre-built styled components |
| `View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, `TextInput` manually styled | `Box`, `Text`, `Button`, `Input`, `Card`, etc. |
| No built-in dark mode | Built-in theme with light/dark modes |
| No design system | Consistent token-based spacing, colors, typography |
| Reinvent forms, modals, alerts every project | Ready-made `Modal`, `Alert`, `Toast`, `Select`, etc. |

---

## Installation

```bash
# 1. Create Expo app
npx create-expo-app@latest MyApp
cd MyApp

# 2. Install GlueStack UI
npx gluestack-ui init

# 3. Install NativeWind (GlueStack v2 dependency)
npm install nativewind tailwindcss
```

Wrap the app in `GluestackUIProvider`:

```tsx
// app/_layout.tsx
import { GluestackUIProvider } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';
import { config } from '@gluestack-ui/config';
import { Stack } from 'expo-router';

export default function RootLayout() {
    return (
        <GluestackUIProvider config={config}>
            <Stack />
        </GluestackUIProvider>
    );
}
```

