## Core Component Mapping

### Layout: div → Box / VStack / HStack

**React Web:**

```tsx
// Vertical stack
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-4 bg-white">
    <h1>Title</h1>
    <p>Content</p>
</div>

// Horizontal row
<div className="flex flex-row items-center gap-2">
    <img src={icon} />
    <span>Label</span>
</div>
```

**GlueStack:**

```tsx
import { Box, VStack, HStack, Text, Heading } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';

// Vertical stack
<VStack space="md" p="$4" bg="$white">
    <Heading>Title</Heading>
    <Text>Content</Text>
</VStack>

// Horizontal row
<HStack space="sm" alignItems="center">
    <Image source={{ uri: icon }} style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />
    <Text>Label</Text>
</HStack>
```

> `VStack` = vertical flex column. `HStack` = horizontal flex row. `Box` = generic `View` with style props.

---

### Typography: h1–h6, p, span → Heading / Text

**React Web:**

```tsx
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Product Title</h1>
<h2 className="text-xl font-semibold">Subtitle</h2>
<p className="text-base text-gray-600">Description text</p>
<span className="text-sm text-red-500">Error message</span>
```

**GlueStack:**

```tsx
import { Heading, Text } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';

<Heading size="3xl">Product Title</Heading>
<Heading size="xl">Subtitle</Heading>
<Text size="md" color="$coolGray600">Description text</Text>
<Text size="sm" color="$error500">Error message</Text>
```

GlueStack `size` tokens: `"2xs"` | `"xs"` | `"sm"` | `"md"` | `"lg"` | `"xl"` | `"2xl"` | `"3xl"` | `"4xl"` | `"5xl"` | `"6xl"`

---

### Button: `<button>` → `<Button>`

**React Web:**

```tsx
<button
    onClick={handleSubmit}
    disabled={loading}
    className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-blue-700"
>
    {loading ? 'Saving...' : 'Submit'}
</button>

// Danger button
<button onClick={handleDelete} className="bg-red-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
    Delete
</button>
```

**GlueStack:**

```tsx
import { Button, ButtonText, ButtonSpinner } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';

<Button onPress={handleSubmit} isDisabled={loading} action="primary">
    {loading ? <ButtonSpinner /> : <ButtonText>Submit</ButtonText>}
</Button>

// Danger button
<Button onPress={handleDelete} action="negative">
    <ButtonText>Delete</ButtonText>
</Button>
```

Button `action` values: `"primary"` | `"secondary"` | `"positive"` | `"negative"` | `"default"`
Button `variant` values: `"solid"` | `"outline"` | `"link"`

---

### Input: `<input>` → `<Input>` + `<InputField>`

**React Web:**

```tsx
<input
    type="text"
    value={name}
    onChange={e => setName(e.target.value)}
    placeholder="Enter product name"
    className="border rounded px-3 py-2 w-full focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
/>
```

**GlueStack:**

```tsx
import { Input, InputField } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';

<Input variant="outline" size="md" isInvalid={!!errors.name}>
    <InputField
        value={name}
        onChangeText={setName}
        placeholder="Enter product name"
        autoCapitalize="none"
    />
</Input>
```

> `Input` is the container (handles border, focus ring, error state). `InputField` is the actual text input.

---

### Textarea

**React Web:**

```tsx
<textarea
    value={description}
    onChange={e => setDescription(e.target.value)}
    rows={4}
    className="border rounded p-3 w-full"
/>
```

**GlueStack:**

```tsx
import { Textarea, TextareaInput } from '@gluestack-ui/themed';

<Textarea size="md" isInvalid={!!errors.description}>
    <TextareaInput
        value={description}
        onChangeText={setDescription}
        placeholder="Enter description..."
        numberOfLines={4}
    />
</Textarea>
```

